      "Microbiology",
      "Genetics",
      "Biochemistry"
    ]
  },
  "work_experience": "Work placements and volunteering can provide healthcare experience and help when applying to college, university, or a new job with NHSScotland.",
  "education_and_training": {
    "training_programmes": [
      "Scientist Training Programme (STP) — 3-year work-based programme.",
      "Alternative work-based training programme — 3-year programme offered by some health boards."
    ],
    "registration": "On completion, register as a clinical scientist with the HCPC.",
    "equivalence_route": "Bioinformaticians with significant NHS embryology experience can apply for equivalence recognition by submitting a portfolio to the Academy for Healthcare Science or Association of Clinical Scientists and attending an interview."
  },
  "learning_and_development": {
    "overview": "Clinical embryologists must undertake CPD to keep knowledge and skills up to date and maintain HCPC registration.",
    "further_qualifications": [
      "Higher specialist development",
      "PhDs and professional doctorates"
    ]
  },
  "career_progression": {
    "overview": "Gaining qualifications leads to more senior roles or advancement into specialised practice areas.",
